stateDiagram-v2
  direction LR

  state "Job lifecycle" as J {
    [*] --> J_PENDING: POST /transcribe<br/>(job + chunks committed atomically)
    J_PENDING --> J_PROCESSING: first chunk picked up
    J_PROCESSING --> J_COMPLETED: all chunks COMPLETED<br/>→ stitch → deid → persist
    J_PROCESSING --> J_COMPLETED_WITH_ERRORS: ≥1 chunk FAILED, ≥1 COMPLETED<br/>failed chunks inlined as [chunk N unavailable]
    J_PROCESSING --> J_FAILED: all chunks FAILED
    J_COMPLETED --> [*]
    J_COMPLETED_WITH_ERRORS --> [*]
    J_FAILED --> [*]
  }

  state "Chunk lifecycle (per audio path)" as CH {
    [*] --> C_PENDING: enqueued
    C_PENDING --> C_PROCESSING: worker acquires ASR permit
    C_PROCESSING --> C_COMPLETED: 200 → persist text
    C_PROCESSING --> C_RETRY: 500 / timeout (transient, ~1/20)<br/>release permit · backoff + jitter
    C_RETRY --> C_PROCESSING: attempt ≤ 4
    C_RETRY --> C_FAILED: attempts exhausted (poison chunk)
    C_PROCESSING --> C_FAILED: 404 (permanent, no retry)
    C_PROCESSING --> C_PENDING: worker crash →<br/>permit TTL expires · task redelivered<br/>(idempotent handler re-checks status)
    C_COMPLETED --> [*]
    C_FAILED --> [*]
  }

  note right of CH
    Invariants:
    • every transition persisted to Postgres before acted on
    • terminal states immutable
    • reconciler re-enqueues anything stuck > deadline
    • 429 from ASR = limiter bug → circuit breaker + alert
  end note
